""RATED
  One of the most popular food joints in Bangalore. Been to bangalore and not had their burgers? That happened last time I was in Bangalore.
This time around I made sure that I go and try their burger and dessert. This place is usually crowded but they have really quick service.
We went for their All American Cheese Burger (Xl) Ordering a Xl burger at this place was a huge mistake because of its size. It was huge that we couldn't get a proper bite of it . I know it's not their fault just a personal opinion. But I must say it's the best burger I have ever had. 2 of us couldn't finish the burger. It was extremely heavy. But the flavors were bang on. Who doesn't love cheeseee. Loved their cheesy patty.
For the dessert we had Mississippi mud pie. I just have to say that I am coming back to this place to have it. It was amazing! I am sucker for good desert and this was one. One of my personal favorites.
Can't wait to visit them again. Loved their food ÃÂÃÂ°ÃÂ\x9fÃÂ\x99ÃÂ\x88"")

""RATED
  This pub is very happening if the sole purpose is to dance and enjoy. It has one of the best dance floor setup and the music is too loud that you cant hear anything else. This place is to forget everything and dance.

We went their to celebrate one of our friend's birthday. We were awestruck by the ambience and lighting and all the setup. DJ started by 10 and then the environment was just phenomenal. Everyone was dancing and enjoying themselves.

The only flaw is the taste of their food. It was not that bad but its not that good to. We ordered many starters and none of them impressed me. So if you are planning to have food also then you might give a thought.

If food is not a concebt then you must visit this place if you like dancing and pubs. There are many events which keeps on organising every week and you can get free passes on many of the event organising apps."")

name: ('Rated 5.0'
address:
it is a lovable Bawa place to the core. Very friendly nice and smiling servers. Loved the friendly vibes.
The food and drinks were lip smacking- now when have Parsi joints ever gone wrong with food.
We ordered The Chicken Pav Cutlet and Tareli Macchi to go with our cocktails- a normal gin tonic( finding frenny) and a raspberry vodka.
Perfectly cooked and succulent.
Then came the main course- had to be the typical Dhansaak (mutton) and the Berry Pulao Chicken. Both were satisfying and reminded me so much of my Bombay days.
A huge shoutout to you guys at SodaBottleOpenerWala . You guys Rock !!')

  The first thing you will notice is that they have a massive place on such prime location and they have made the most of the place. Good ambience for a bunch of friends to hang out and chill with a round of drinks.

The prices of the drinks go up as people order it and the prices of drinks go down as they are not favoured for the day. Pretty simple concept and made very interesting with a stock market concept.
